## Core SQL Commands (Refresher)

### Database Operations

```sql
SHOW DATABASES;
CREATE DATABASE db_name;
USE db_name;
```

### Table Operations

```sql
SHOW TABLES;

CREATE TABLE users (
    name VARCHAR(100)
);
```

### Data Operations

```sql
INSERT INTO users VALUES ('alice');
INSERT INTO users VALUES ('bob');

SELECT * FROM users;
```

### Delete / Drop

```sql
DROP DATABASE db_name;
```

---

## Useful Built-in Functions

```sql
SELECT USER();
SELECT VERSION();
SELECT DATABASE();
```

- `USER()` → current DB user (e.g., root@localhost)
- `VERSION()` → DB version
- `DATABASE()` → current DB (NULL if none selected)

